Diagnosis
(female). Mesal stripe of setation reaching dorsal edge of scrobal depression. Antenna completely black (Delvare 2017: fig. 26). Fasciae on mesoscutum, GT5 and GT6 with silvery setation (Delvare 2017: figs 26‒ 28). Metafemur densely setose and punctulate all over (
Fig. 58
). Spiracles on GT6 with elevated rim forming truncate cones (
Fig. 58
). Ovipositor sheaths 5.85× as long as the carinate dorsal edge of syntergum and 1.62× as long as mesosoma (Delvare 2017: fig. 26).
